#, no-c-format
msgid "Planning for &productname;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:14
#, no-c-format
msgid "This chapter describes some basic considerations before installing &productname;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: planning.xml:25
#, no-c-format
msgid "Considerations for deployment of <phrase os=\"sles\">&sls;</phrase> <phrase os=\"slemicro\">&slem;</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "The implementation of an operating system either in an existing IT environment or as a completely new rollout must be carefully prepared. At the beginning of the planning process, you should try to define the project goals and necessary features. This must always be done individually for each project, but the questions to answer should include the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "How many installations should be done? Depending on this, the best deployment methods differ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:44
#, no-c-format
msgid "Will the system run as physical host or as a virtual machine?"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "Will the system be exposed to external threats like hacker attacks? <phrase os=\"sles;sled;osuse\"> Have a look at <xref linkend=\"cha-security\"/> to get an overview of consequences.</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "How will you get regular updates? All patches are provided online for registered users in the <link xlink:href=\"&sccurl;\">&scc;</link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:63
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do you need help for your local installation? &suse; provides training, support, and consulting for all topics pertaining to <phrase os=\"sles\">&sls;</phrase> <phrase os=\"slemicro\">&slem;</phrase> . Find more information about this at <link xlink:href=\"https://www.suse.com/products/server/\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:73
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do you need third-party products? Make sure that the required product is also supported on the desired platform. &suse; can provide help to support software on different platforms when needed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: planning.xml:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "Deployment of <phrase os=\"sles\">&sls;</phrase> <phrase os=\"slemicro\">&slem;</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:84
#, no-c-format
msgid "To make sure that your system will run flawlessly, always try to use certified hardware. The hardware certification process is an ongoing process and the database of certified hardware is updated regularly. Find the search form for certified hardware at <link xlink:href=\"https://www.suse.com/yessearch/Search.jsp\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "Depending on the number of desired installations, it is beneficial to use installation servers or even completely automatic installations. <phrase os=\"sles\"> When using &xen; or &kvm; virtualization technologies, network root file systems or network storage solutions like iSCSI should be considered.</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "In case you intend to install only several nodes of &slema;, you can choose the manual installation or you can directly deploy pre-built images. For a large-scale deployment it is recommended to use the automatic installation by using &ay;, &susemgr;, or wherever you can easily copy the pre-built images to the desired machines, you can also use the pre-built images for a large-scale deployment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase os=\"sles\">&sls;</phrase> <phrase os=\"slemicro\">&slem;</phrase> provides you with a broad variety of services. Most of the needed configurations can be made with &yast;, the &suse; configuration utility. In addition, many manual configurations are described in the corresponding chapters."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "In addition to the plain software installation, you should consider training the end users of the systems and help desk staff."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: planning.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminology"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the following sections, the system to hold your new &productname; installation is called <emphasis>target system</emphasis> or <emphasis>installation target</emphasis> . The term <emphasis>repository</emphasis> (previously called <quote>installation source</quote> ) is used for all sources of installation data. This includes physical media, such as CD, DVD, or &usbflashdrive;, and network servers distributing the installation data in your network."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: planning.xml:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running <phrase os=\"sles\">&sls;</phrase> <phrase os=\"slemicro\">&slem;</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:139
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <phrase os=\"sles\">&sls;</phrase> <phrase os=\"slemicro\">&slem;</phrase> operating system is a well-tested and stable system. Unfortunately, this does not prevent hardware failures or other causes for downtime or data loss. Make sure that you have a backup solution in place for mission-critical tasks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:147
#, no-c-format
msgid "For optimal security and data safety, you should make regular updates of all the operated machines. If you have a mission critical server, you should run a second identical (pre-production) machine that you can use to test all changes. This also gives you the possibility of switching machines in case of hardware failure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: planning.xml:156
#, no-c-format
msgid "Registering &productname;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:158
#, no-c-format
msgid "To get technical support and product updates, you need to register and activate your &suse; product with the &scc;. We recommend to register during the installation, since this will enable you to install the system with the latest updates and patches available. However, if you are offline or want to skip the registration step, you can complete registration from the running system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:167
#, no-c-format
msgid "In case your organization does not provide a local registration server, registering &sle; requires a &scc; account. In case you do not have one yet, go to the &scc; home page ( <link xlink:href=\"https://scc.suse.com/\"/> ) to create one."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:174
#, no-c-format
msgid "During the installation you will be asked to enter your registration code. For details, see <xref linkend=\"sec-yast-install-scc-registration\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:180
#, no-c-format
msgid "During the manual installation you will be asked to enter your registration code. For details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-registration\"/> . If you deploy &slema; pre-built images, you need to register your system after the installation, for details refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-images-registration\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you deploy your instances automatically using &ay;, you can register the system during the installation by providing the respective information in the &ay; control file. For details, see <xref linkend=\"CreateProfile-Register\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: planning.xml:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "For registering an already installed system, see <xref linkend=\"sec-yast-software-register\"/> ."
msgstr ""

